lookups.description: Immediate, life-saving intervention required without delay. Example: Cardiac arrest, Massive bleeding

lookups.label: Emergent
lookups.description: High risk of deterioration, or signs of a time-critical problem. Example: Cardiac-related chest pain Asthma attack

lookups.label: Urgent
lookups.description: Stable, with multiple types of resources needed to investigate or treat (such as lab tests plus X-ray imaging). Example: Abdominal pain High fever with cough

lookups.label: LessUrgent
lookups.description: Stable, with only one type of resource anticipated (such as only an X-ray, or only sutures). Example: Simple laceration Pain on urination

lookups.label: Nonurgent
lookups.description: Stable, with no resources anticipated except oral or topical medications, or prescriptions. Example: Rash Prescription refill
